parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air suspension compressor can cause the vehicle to ride unevenly, leading to loss of control, accidents, or damage to the vehicle. It can also cause the suspension fault light to come on, indicating a problem with the suspension system.
symptoms: The suspension fault light comes on
the vehicle rides unevenly
the compressor makes a loud noise
the vehicle's height cannot be adjusted
the suspension system fails to operate properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Tire Wear due to Suspension Alignment Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature tire wear can lead to blowouts, loss of control, and accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Uneven tire wear
exposed plys on the inner part of the rear tires
loud noise in the cabin
vibration while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of problems, including loss of critical systems, accidents, and fires.
symptoms: Radio stops working
loud chime with a suspension fault message
electrical system malfunctions
fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uneven tire wear can lead to reduced traction, increased stopping distances, and a higher risk of tire failure, which can cause accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Uneven wear on the inside or outside of the tires
premature tire wear
loud noise in the cabin
difficulty locating the wear due to its location on the inside treads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty transmission software can cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk when shifting gears, leading to unexpected loss of acceleration, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Harsh and irregular shifting when rolling to a stop and re-accelerating
delayed acceleration from a stop or slow speed
hesitation when attempting to accelerate
transmission slips then engages hard when taking off
vehicle drops out of gear when slowing down or turning
high RPM with no movement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission control module can cause the vehicle to shift out of gear unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle automatically shifts out of park and drives forward
vehicle drops out of gear when slowing down or turning
high RPM with no movement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty transmission calibration can cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk when shifting gears, leading to unexpected loss of acceleration, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Delayed acceleration from a stop or slow speed
hesitation when attempting to accelerate
transmission slips then engages hard when taking off
poor low-speed transmission shifts.
